div.p:
We have been advised of the desire of the Government of Liberia to carry out
                    certain new projects of public works, among which are: 
                        (a)

to move its Capital to a new location in the interior at a cost of
                            several millions of dollars;
                        (b)

to install a sewage and water supply;
                        (c)

to construct a hydroelectric plant for power;
                        (d)

to construct a railroad for the development of the interior;
                        (e)

to hold a Centennial celebration in 1947 which will require
                            substantial new construction and financing;
                        (f)

to construct a stadium at a cost of $300,000.
